[gd_scene load_steps=12 format=3]

; The M3 gate room: "a single room with 3 enemies is a genuinely fun fight."
;
; Deliberately a FLAT pit. The fight should be about spacing, reading telegraphs
; and choosing roll-vs-parry — not about platforming.
;
; It started with two low ledges as escape valves, and they jammed every enemy
; solid. The geometry does not allow it: a ledge low enough to jump onto from the
; floor (109 px of rise, 30 px thick) leaves only ~50 px of headroom underneath,
; which is less than the player's 56 px, never mind the Brute's 88. A platform
; you can reach from the floor is a STEP, not an overhang — anything that walks
; under it gets stuck inside it. Real verticality needs a taller room and a
; two-stage climb; that is M4's job, along with the follow camera.
;
; The roster is a triangle on purpose:
;   Brute (purple, slow, 750 ms telegraph)  -> the parry teacher. Huge reward.
;   Dart  (green, lunges across the room)   -> the roll teacher. Greedy to parry.
;   Grunt (red, generalist)                 -> pressure while you deal with those.

